        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 4:33AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 432 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles east of Denton, or 18 miles northwest of Lewistown, moving east
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Danvers, Hilger, and Christina.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
